If you&rsquo;ve been reading much bpf code recently, you&rsquo;ve probably seen this:
#include &quot;vmlinux.h&quot; vmlinux.h is generated code, it contains all of the type definitions that your running linux kernel uses in it&rsquo;s own source code. This is an important and possibly strange concept to wrap your head around so let me explain.
When you build linux one of the output artifacts is a file called vmlinux. It&rsquo;s also typically packaged with major distributions.
